    "etymology": "[OE., p. p. of forlesen to lose utterly, AS. forle (p. p. forloren); pref. for- + le (in comp.) to lose; cf. D. verliezen to lose, G. verlieren, Sw. f, Dan. forloren, Goth. fraliusan to lose. See For-, and Lorn, a., Lose, v. t.]"
